Considerably rework sentence splitting, so that it now supports a model where line breaks can have 3 treatments: ignored, every line break is also a sentence break, or two consecutive line breaks represent a paragraph/sentence break (traditional hard line-wrapping text). PTBTokenizerAnnotator: Make only class variable final. StanfordCoreNLP: Various changes for new methods in WordstoSentencesAnnotator (now immutable), but in particular add support for ssplit.newlineIsSentenceBreak property, and replace bad \n usages with println(). TokenizerAnnotator: Correct println and add @Override. WordsToSentencesAnnotator: Make immutable, including making only member variable final, change most constructors, add new static factory for nonSplitter. WordToSentenceProcessor: Make immutable, add to documentation, add support for different treatment of line breaks, change a lot of constructors, delete many (mutating) methods. ArrayUtils: Add asImmutableSet() method. WordsToSentencesAnnotatorTest: Add second test. WordToSentenceProcessorTest: Update for new constructors and add a number of new tests. SubcatParserTrainer, StringToAnnotatedWordsPipeline: Update for API changes in other classes.
